                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363 Am 6/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-07T21:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1921—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 8(<hi rend="smallcaps">?</hi>)—11:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Congress this evening rejected Amory concession protocol by 24 to 10 votes.
                    Will report promptly any consequences.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
